        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Tested this locally. In local testing, I found that \"make all\" was failing in multicloud:\n> \n> [multicloud]\n> make[1]: Entering directory '/home/ubuntu/oom/kubernetes'\n> Error: error unpacking multicloud-k8s in multicloud: chart metadata (Chart.yaml) missing\n> Makefile:42: recipe for target 'dep-multicloud' failed\n> make[1]: *** [dep-multicloud] Error 1\n> make[1]: Leaving directory '/home/ubuntu/oom/kubernetes'\n> Makefile:35: recipe for target 'multicloud' failed\n> make: *** [multicloud] Error 2\n> \n> However, I was able to work around this by doing :\n> make all ; make onap ; make sdnc ; make cds\n> \n> After doing that, confirmed via kubectl describe pod that correct image versions were being loaded\n\nStrike that - kubectl get pods show containers up, but sdnc container is not healthy.  Will put this back into WIP state until local testing passes.",
